item.title: CVE-2018-10900|2024-08-05T07:54:36.169Z -- %5Bunknown%5D -- networkmanager-vpnc
item.description: Network Manager VPNC plugin (aka networkmanager-vpnc) before version 1.2.6 is vulnerable to a privilege escalation attack. A new line character can be used to inject a Password helper parameter into the configuration data passed to VPNC, allowing an attacker to execute arbitrary commands as root.
